Sentencas: A theoretical model for a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a bi-layer electrolyte is developed and analytical solutions of various important relationships, such as I V relationship, distribution of oxygen partial pressure in the bi-layer electrolyte, leakage current density etc. are obtained.
Titulo: An analytical model for solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: Based on the assumptions of constant ionic conductivity and reversible electrodes, the model takes into considerations of transports of both ions and electrons in the electrolyte.
Titulo: An analytical model for solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: The modeling results are compared with both experimental data and results from other models in the literature and very good agreements are obtained.
Titulo: An analytical model for solid oxide fuel cells with bi-layer electrolyte
